request.description:
### Get User Favourites

This endpoint retrieves the authenticated user's favourite items across multiple asset types: charts, insights, and audiences. It supports pagination to allow users to navigate large result sets.

---

### Request

- **Method:** `GET`
- **URL:** `http://localhost:3008/v1/user/favourites`
- **Headers:**  
    `Authorization: Bearer`
- **Query Parameters:**


| Parameter | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `pageSize` | integer | (Optional) Number of items per page (default: 10) |
| `pageNumber` | integer | (Optional) Page number to retrieve (default: 0) |

---

### Response

- **Success Status:** `200 OK`
- **Content-Type:** `application/json`


### Response Body

The response contains the following fields:

- `data`: An object with the user's favourite assets.
- `pagination`: Pagination information.


### Data Structure

``` json
{
  "data": {
    "charts": [
      {
        "id": "string",
        "description": "string",
        "info": {
          "id": "string",
          "title": "string",
          "x_axis_title": "string",
          "y_axis_title": "string",
          "data": [
            {
              "x": number,
              "y": number
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ],
    "insights": [
      {
        "id": "string",
        "description": "string",
        "info": {
          "Id": "string",
          "Text": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "audiences": [
      {
        "id": "string",
        "description": "string",
        "info": {
          "id": "string",
          "gender": "string",
          "birth_country": "string",
          "age_group": "string",
          "social_media_hours": number,
          "purchases_last_month": number
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "pagination": {
    "page": number,
    "pageSize": number,
    "maxPage": number
  }
}

 ```

---

### Error Responses

#### Structure

All error responses have the following format:

``` json
{
  "error": "string"
}

 ```

#### Possible Error Codes

| Status Code | Message | Cause |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `400` | `"Invalid query params"` | Malformed or invalid `pageSize` or `pageNumber` |
| `401` | `"Unauthorized"` | Missing or invalid JWT token (from middleware) |
| `500` | `"Internal Server Error"` | Unexpected error while processing the request |

---

#### Example Success Response

``` json
{
  "data": {
    "charts": [
      {
        "id": "chart1",
        "description": "Sales over time",
        "info": {
          "id": "info1",
          "title": "Monthly Sales",
          "x_axis_title": "Month",
          "y_axis_title": "Revenue",
          "data": [
            { "x": 1, "y": 1000 },
            { "x": 2, "y": 1200 }
          ]
        }
      }
    ],
    "insights": [
      {
        "id": "insight1",
        "description": "Customer retention trend",
        "info": {
          "Id": "i1",
          "Text": "Retention improved by 15% this quarter"
        }
      }
    ],
    "audiences": [
      {
        "id": "aud1",
        "description": "Young social users",
        "info": {
          "id": "a1",
          "gender": "Female",
          "birth_country": "USA",
          "age_group": "18-24",
          "social_media_hours": 5,
          "purchases_last_month": 3
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "pagination": {
    "page": 0,
    "pageSize": 10,
    "maxPage": 2
  }
}

 ```

---

#### Example Error Response

``` json
{
  "error": "Internal Server Error"
}

 ```
